issue.title: [Feature Request]: add an option to highres.fix to save or stop after first pass
issue.body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues and checked the recent builds/commits

### What would your feature do ?

Enabling highres.fix for large images is a great feature, but sometimes when it gets at 50% (or first pass) the image is better (subjectively speaking) than the final image. 

The idea would be to add a new checkbox inside the "Highres.fix" option, or in the settings tab. Either to save after first pass, or to just do a single pass.

### Proposed workflow

1. Enable "Highres.fix"
2. Set with, height and denoise streng
3. Check a new box called "single pass" (or save first pass)
4. and then click "Generate" 


### Additional information

The option to save or stop is mentioned here as I don't know what is best for development, Either way, having an image just after the first pass would be great. Thanks!

issue.title: Allow tranform func to be async
issue.body: If the user passes in an async function for the transform option then mongoosastic will silently the ditch all fields in the document being indexed in elasticsearch. This is because it doesn't understand that it's an async function and thus doesn't wait for it to resolve. This MR fixes that by respecting the fact that an async function may be given and waits till the promise is resolved.

issue.title: Allow tranform func to be async
issue.body: If the user passes in an async function for the transform option then mongoosastic will silently the ditch all fields in the document being indexed in elasticsearch. This is because it doesn't understand that it's an async function and thus doesn't wait for it to resolve. This MR fixes that by respecting the fact that an async function may be given and waits till the promise is resolved.
